stinct irreducible cubic equations over ℚ, no nontrivial rational linear relation among 1, m, n can exist.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"h₁\",\n        \"h₂\",\n        \"irreducibility of x^3-2 over ℚ\",\n        \"irreducibility of x^3-4 over ℚ\",\n        \"linear independence from distinct algebraic extensions\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"a = 0, b = 0, and c = 0.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The hypothesis h₃ is exactly a rational linear relation a + b m + c n = 0. By the linear independence established in the previous step, all coefficients must be zero.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"h₃\",\n        \"step 3\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"a = 0 ∧ b = 0 ∧ c = 0\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization.\n\n## Previous attempt (failed)\nYour last formalization:\n{\"theorem\":{\"variables\":[{\"name\":\"m\",\"sort\":\"Real\"},{\"name\":\"n\",\"sort\":\"Real\"},{\"name\":\"a\",\"sort\":\"Real\"},{\"name\":\"b\",\"sort\":\"Real\"},{\"name\":\"c\",\"sort\":\"Real\"}],\"hypotheses\":[\"And(0 < m, 0 < n)\",\"m**3 == 2\",\"n**3 == 4\",\"a + b*m + c*n == 0\"],\"goal\":\"And(a == 0, b == 0, c == 0)\"},\"functions\":[],\"lemmas\":[{\"name\":\"cube_root_distinct_linear_independence\",\"english\":\"If m and n are positive real numbers satisfying m^3=2 and n^3=4, then any real linear relation a + b*m + c*n = 0 forces a=b=c=0.\",\"vars\":[{\"name\":\"m\",\"sort\":\"Real\"},{\"name\":\"n\",\"sort\":\"Real\"},{\"name\":\"a\",\"sort\":\"Real\"},{\"name\":\"b\",\"sort\":\"Real\"},{\"name\":\"c\",\"sort\":\"Real\"}],\"body\":\"Implies(And(0 < m, 0 < n, m**3 == 2, n**3 == 4, a + b*m + c*n == 0), And(a == 0, b == 0, c == 0))\"}],\"instantiations\":[{\"lemma\":\"cube_root_distinct_linear_independence\",\"terms\":{\"m\":\"m\",\"n\":\"n\",\"a\":\"a\",\"b\":\"b\",\"c\":\"c\"}}]}\n\nErrors:\n- lemma(s) ['cube_root_distinct_linear_independence'] are contradictory; refusing to certify\n\nFix these issues and return the corrected JSON object only.