    "content": "## Theorem: algebra_sqineq_unitcircatbpabsamblt1\n\nTheorem: algebra_sqineq_unitcircatbpabsamblt1\nVariables: a, b (real)\nGiven: h₀ : a^2 + b^2 = 1\nProve: a * b + ∥a - b∥ ≤ 1\n\nGoal: a * b + ∥a - b∥ ≤ 1\n\n## English proof (from stage 1)\n{\n  \"key_observation\": \"Use the identity (a - b)^2 + 2ab = a^2 + b^2 = 1 and split into the cases a ≥ b and a < b, so the absolute value becomes ±(a - b) and the left-hand side can be rewritten as a linear expression bounded by 1.\",\n  \"plan\": [\n    \"Rewrite the constraint a^2 + b^2 = 1 as an identity involving (a - b)^2 and ab.\",\n    \"Consider the case a ≥ b, where |a - b| = a - b.\",\n    \"Consider the case a < b, where |a - b| = b - a.\",\n    \"In each case, reduce the target inequality to a simple bound using nonnegativity of squares.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"From a^2 + b^2 = 1, we have (a - b)^2 = 1 - 2ab.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Expand (a - b)^2 = a^2 - 2աբ + b^2 and substitute a^2 + b^2 = 1. Rearranging gives the stated identity.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"algebraic expansion\",\n        \"hypothesis h₀\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"If a ≥ b, then a*b + |a - b| ≤ 1.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"In this case |a - b| = a - b, so the left-hand side is ab + a - b. Using step 1, we get 1 - (a - b)^2 = 2ab, hence ab + a - b = 1 - (a - b)^2/2 + (a - b) - ? More directly, set t = a - b ≥ 0; then step 1 gives 2ab = 1 - t^2, so the expression becomes (1 - t^2)/2 + t = 1 - (t - 1)^2/2 ≤ 1.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 1\",\n        \"definition of absolute value\",\n        \"nonnegativity of squares\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"If a < b, then a*b + |a - b| ≤ 1.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"In this case |a - b| = b - a. Let t = b - a > 0. Then (a - b)^2 = t^2, so step 1 again gives 2ab = 1 - t^2. The expression becomes (1 - t^2)/2 + t = 1 - (t - 1)^2/2 ≤ 1.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 1\",\n        \"definition of absolute value\",\n        \"nonnegativity of squares\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"In all cases, a*b + |a - b| ≤ 1.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The real numbers are ordered, so either a ≥ b or a < b. The previous two steps cover both cases, establishing the desired inequality.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"law of trichotomy\",\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"step 3\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": null\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
